        <div class="description">
          So let’s get even faster. Many websites want to be faster than their competitors. Studies show that if you are 20% faster than your competitor you begin to ‘steal’ their competition. To study and work towards this goal Patrick Meenan invented a metric called Speed Index that refers to the visual completeness of a site as it progresses through loading. The average Speed Index (in January 2016) was around 5400 (or the NFL player) But the top 10th percentile was closer to 1300 (the image below)! <strong>Perspective</strong> - this spring two engineers built the rubik cube solving robot that could solve it in just over 1.2 seconds. This robot could solve three rubik cubes before the average webpage loads.
        </div>
        <a href="http://www.techinsider.io/robot-solves-rubiks-cube-in-one-second-2016-1" target="_blank" class="ui segment large image blog-image">
